quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,43,"And We did not send (messengers) before you other than men whom We inspired with revelation. So, ask the people (having the knowledge) of the Message, if you do not know."
  16,44,"(We sent them) with clear signs and scriptures. And We sent down the Message (The Qur'an) so that you explain to the people what has been revealed for them and so that they may ponder."
  16,45,"Do they who contrive evil plots feel immune from that Allah makes the earth cave in with them, or from that the punishment comes to them from where they would not perceive,"
  16,46,"or that He seizes them while roaming about - while they are not to frustrate Him -"
  16,47,"or that He seizes them while they are in apprehension? So, in-deed your Lord is Very Kind, Very Merciful."
  16,48,"Have they not observed things Allah has created, their shadows inclining from the right and the left prostrating before Allah, while they are humble?"
  16,49,"And to Allah prostrates whatever creature there is in the heavens and in the earth, and the angels, and they show no arrogance."
  16,50,"They fear their Lord above them and do as they are commanded."
  16,51,"And Allah has said, 'Do not take to yourselves two gods. He is but One God. So, Me alone you fear.""
  16,52,"And to Him belongs what is in the heavens and the earth and it is only He who deserves obedience as due. Would you, then, fear someone other than Allah?"
  16,53,"And whatever blessing you have is from Allah. Then, once you are touched by distress, to Him alone you cry for help."
  16,54,"Then, as soon as He removes the distress from you, a group from among you starts ascribing partners to their Lord."